<HL>
   General Sekiyu Posts Profit
</HL>
<DATE>
06/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   J.GSK
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   TOKYO -- General Sekiyu KK, a Japanese oil refiner,
reported that consolidated pretax profit for the year ended
March 31 fell 69% to 5.34 billion yen ($34.9 million) from
17.04 billion yen a year earlier, but net income rose 41% to
11.59 billion yen, or 57.14 yen a share, from 8.25 billion
yen, or 50.4 yen a share.
   The company sold 11.25 billion yen in fixed assets in
fiscal 1990, a rise of 10.89 billion yen from the
year-earlier level. Sales rose 13% to 472.03 billion yen from
417.79 billion yen. Cost of sales, which includes oil
acquisition costs, rose to 413.14 billion yen from 349.11
billion yen.
