<HL>
   Business Brief -- Towle Manufacturing Co.:
   Certain Assets to Be Sold
   To Fieldston Investors L.P.
</HL>
<DATE>
06/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6G
</SO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
</IN>
<LP>
   Towle Manufacturing Co., Newburyport, Mass., currently
operating under Chapter 11 of the U.S. Bankruptcy Code, said
it signed a definitive agreement with Fieldston Investors
Limited Partnership, a private New York investment concern,
for the sale of certain assets of its silversmiths, retail,
Canada and Hong Kong businesses.
   Terms weren't disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The agreement, already approved by Towle's board, requires
the approval of the U.S. bankruptcy court. With approval,
Towle said it expects to close the transaction within about
60 days.
   Fieldston said it intends to continue operating the
businesses after the sale.
   Towle is a maker of silver and giftware products.
</TEXT>
