<HL>
   International Brief -- Yaskawa Electric Manufacturing:
   Fiscal-Year Pretax Earnings
   Rose 39% to $61.1 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
06/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   J.YSK
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Yaskawa Electric Manufacturing Co., a leading Japanese
maker of motors, said its consolidated pretax profit for the
year ended March 20 increased 39% to 9.33 billion yen ($61.1
million) from 6.73 billion yen a year earlier.
   Net income rose 24% to 3.71 billion yen, or 16.18 yen a
share, from 2.99 billion yen, or 13.20 yen a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales increased 16% to 201.26 billion yen from 173.54
billion yen.
   Sales of robots and related equipment grew 20% to 100.516
billion yen, helped by brisk demand for industrial robots.
Manufacturing systems sales rose 10% to 32.95 billion yen,
because of increased investment in facilities by the steel
and the paper and pulp industries. Sales of heavy electric
machinery increased 7.9% to 62.89 billion yen.
   Yaskawa predicted consolidated pretax profit for fiscal
1991 will increase to 10.2 billion yen, an indicated rise of
9.3%. Net income is expected to rise to 4.2 billion yen, or
13%, and sales to 221 billion yen, or 9.8%.
</TEXT>
