   Rose to 7.6% in May
</HL>
<DATE>
06/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canada's unemployment rate rose to 7.6% of the
work force in May from 7.2% in April, Statistics Canada, a
federal agency, said.
   The rise was attributed to a weakening trend in the
Canadian economy.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Manufacturing employment fell sharply in May for the third
consecutive month.
   Statistics Canada also said its help-wanted index, an
early indicator of labor demand, fell 5.3% in May. The index
monitors changes in help-wanted advertisements in major
Canadian cities.
